XD Bar
-------
A minialistic statusbar, inspired by 'X'mobar and 'D'wm statusbar, for X11
Desktops that are compatible with EWMH standards.

Rendering styled/clickable text, is inspired by xmobar's approach of having
tags in the string (https://xmobar.org/).
Populating statusbar is inspired by dwm statusbar's approach of using the root
window's 'WM_NAME' attribute text (https://dwm.suckless.org/).

Why use C? performance and X11 lib support.
Future Goals: Maybe rewrite in Rust. :pepehands:

Build Requirements:
-------------------
  - gnu make
  - x11
  - xft

Optional Requirements:
---------
  - pkg-config  (update 'config.mk', if 'pkg-config' not installed).
  - lua         (runtime configurations support).

Build and install:
------------------
  Default build:
    $ make

  Build with patches enabled:
    $ make PATCHES="lua xrm ..."

  Install:
    $ sudo make install

Available Patches:
------------------
  lua: runtime config support with lua source file.
  xrm: runtime config support with X Resources.

  (patches are just space seperated c filenames, from 'include/patches/',
    without file extension.)

How bar window renders:
-----------------------

  + - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - margin - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - +
  ¦ +------------------------------------------------------------------------+ ¦
  ¦ | + - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - padding - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -+ | ¦
  ¦ | ¦stdin                                                        WM_NAME¦ | ¦
  ¦ | +- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - + | ¦
  ¦ +------------------------------------------------------------------------+ ¦
  +- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - +

  - 'margin' is the empty space outside of the bar window.
  - 'padding' is the space between the bar window edges and the drawing region.
  - 'stdin' text is typically provided by the window manager
  - 'WM_NAME' (of the root window) can be set using the 'xsetroot' command.

Setting 'WM_NAME':
------------------
  - slstatus <https://tools.suckless.org/slstatus>
  - smolprog <https://github.com/lycuid/smolprog> (much faster and overall just
        better than slstatus...coz. Rust. I guess?).

  - Custom script example (using bash):
    #!/bin/bash
    while true; do
      xsetroot -name "$(whoami)@$(hostname) on $(uname -o) | $(date)"
      sleep(1)
    done

Styling text:
-------------
  Template for styling text:
    <Tag:Extension=Value> Text </Tag>

  Tags:
    Fn, Fg, Bg, Box, BtnL, BtnM, BtnR, ScrlU, ScrlD

  Extensions (Optional):
    Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt, Left, Right, Top, Bottom

  Valid Extensions for Tags:
    ---------------------------------------
    | Tag     | Extensions                |
    ---------------------------------------
    | Fn      | -                         |
    | Fg      | -                         |
    | Bg      | -                         |
    | Box     | Left, Right, Top, Bottom  |
    | BtnL    | Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt   |
    | BtnM    | Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt   |
    | BtnR    | Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt   |
    | ScrlU   | Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt   |
    | ScrlD   | Shift, Ctrl, Super, Alt   |
    ---------------------------------------

  Valid Values for Tags:
    <Fn=Number>
      'Number': index of 'fonts' array in 'config.h'.
      'fonts[0]' will be used as default font.

    <Fg=Color> <Bg=Color>
      'Color': any valid color name.
      - eg. <Fg=black> </Fg>  <Bg=#000000> </Bg>

    <Box=Color> <Box=Color:Size>
      'Color' any valid color name.
      'Size' size in pixels (if not provided, defaults to 1).
      - eg. <Box=yellow:2> </Box>  <Box=#dfdfdf> </Box>

    <BtnL=Command> <BtnM=Command> <BtnR=Command> <ScrlU=Command> <ScrlD=Command>
      'Command' any string. command output/error will not be handled.
      - eg. <BtnL=systemctl poweroff> </BtnL>  <BtnR=systemctl reboot> </BtnR>

Example text:
-------------
  - <Fg=#131313> Colored </Fg> text with <Bg=#c6c6c6> background</Bg>.

  - <Box:Bottom=#ffffff:1> underlined </Bottom> text.

  - <BtnL=systemctl reboot> reboot </BtnL>
  - <BtnL:Shift=sudo -A reboot now> reboot w/ confirmation </BtnL>

  - <ScrlU:Ctrl=amixer sset Master 5%+><ScrlD:Ctrl=amixer sset Master 5%->
      volume
    </ScrlD></ScrlU>
